"text":" instance to set a style that defines","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the control’s appearance and behavior. For example, you can choose","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle\/switch","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" style:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["Toggle(\"Vibrate on Ring\", isOn: $vibrateOnRing)","    .toggleStyle(.switch)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Built-in styles typically have a similar appearance across platforms,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tailored to the platform’s overall style:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Platform","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Appearance"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS, iPadOS","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]]]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Styling-toggles-in-a-hierarchy","type":"heading","text":"Styling toggles in a hierarchy"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can set a style for all toggle instances within a view hierarchy","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"by applying the style modifier to a container view. For example, you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"can apply the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ToggleStyle\/button"},{"text":" style to an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/HStack","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["HStack {","    Toggle(isOn: $isFlagged) {","        Label(\"Flag\", systemImage: \"flag.fill\")","    }","    Toggle(isOn: $isMuted) {","        Label(\"Mute\", systemImage: \"speaker.slash.fill\")","    }","}",".toggleStyle(.button)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example above has the following appearance when "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isFlagged"},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isMuted"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Platform","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Appearance","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS, iPadOS","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Automatic-styling","type":"heading","text":"Automatic styling"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you don’t set a style, OpenSwiftUI assumes a value of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ToggleStyle\/automatic","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", which corresponds to a context-specific","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"default. Specify the automatic style explicitly to override a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"container’s style and revert to the default:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["HStack {","    Toggle(isOn: $isShuffling) {","        Label(\"Shuffle\", systemImage: \"shuffle\")","    }","    Toggle(isOn: $isRepeating) {","        Label(\"Repeat\", systemImage: \"repeat\")","    }","","    Divider()","","    Toggle(\"Enhance Sound\", isOn: $isEnhanced)","        .toggleStyle(.automatic) \/\/ Revert to the default style.","}",".toggleStyle(.button) \/\/ Use button style for toggles in the stack.",".labelStyle(.iconOnly) \/\/ Omit the title from any labels."],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The style that OpenSwiftUI uses as the default depends on both the platform","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and the context. In macOS, the default in most contexts is a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ToggleStyle\/checkbox"},{"text":", while in iOS, the default toggle style is a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle\/switch","type":"reference"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Platform"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Appearance"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS, iPadOS","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Like toggle style does for toggles, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View\/labelStyle(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifier sets the style for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Label"},{"type":"text","text":" instances in the hierarchy. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example above demostrates the compact "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LabelStyle\/iconOnly"},{"type":"text","text":" style,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which is useful for button toggles in space-constrained contexts."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Always include a descriptive title for better accessibility."}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For more information about how OpenSwiftUI chooses a default toggle style,","type"